claim.claim-text:
A resin tube configured to be inserted in a flexible tube of an endoscope or a connection cable, the resin tube comprising:
a first tube including, on a part of an outer surface thereof, a helical-shaped first groove;
a second tube;
a connecting pipe configured to connect one end of the first tube and one end of the second tube; and
a first coil wound on the first groove of the first tube;
wherein the first tube is connected to the connecting pipe at a part where the first groove is formed and the first coil is not wound.
